55.4	Calendula	Calendula	Calendula ( Ca-lén-du-la), pot marigold, is a genus of about 12–20 species of annual or perennial herbaceous plants in the daisy family Asteraceae, native to the area from Macaronesia east through the Mediterranean region to Iran. Calendula should not be confused with other plants that are also known as marigolds, such as corn marigold, desert marigold, marsh marigold, or plants of the genus Tagetes.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/67/Calendula_January_2008-1_filtered.jpg/220px-Calendula_January_2008-1_filtered.jpg
